-- Granite Rises Most in Two Months in Tel Aviv After Tambour Buy
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-05-23T08:55:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-23/granite-rises-most-in-two-months-in-tel-aviv-after-tambour-buy.html
  Granite Hacarmel Investments Ltd. (GRNT) 
advanced the most in more than two months after the marketer of
petroleum and automobile products said it will acquire the
remaining stake in  Tambour Ltd. (TMBU)   The  shares  of Granite climbed 5.1 percent, the biggest
intraday gain since March 21, to 4.1 shekels at 11:52 a.m. in
Tel Aviv.  After the acquisition Granite will hold a 95 percent stake
in Tambour and delist the shares from the Tel Aviv bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
